# Dev Workflow Rules

## 1. Issue Reporting — Always Check Logs First

When the user reports a bug, error, or unexpected behavior, **before responding**, inspect the following log paths:

- `~/.pasture/daemon.log` — main runtime output (`$PASTURE_STATE_DIR/daemon.log` if the env var is set; legacy `$COWCODE_STATE_DIR` / `~/.cowcode` still work)
- `~/.pasture/daemon.err` — daemon stderr / crash output (`$PASTURE_STATE_DIR/daemon.err` if the env var is set)
- `pm2 logs pasture` — Windows / pm2-managed process logs

Use `tail -n 100 ~/.pasture/daemon.log` or `tail -n 100 ~/.pasture/daemon.err` to surface recent entries. Quote the relevant log lines in your reply so the user can see exactly what was captured.

## 2. Adding or Editing a Feature — Tests Are Mandatory

Whenever a feature is added or an existing one is modified:

1. **Find the relevant test** in `scripts/test/` (pattern: `test-<feature>.js` or `test-<feature>-e2e.js`). When adding or changing tests, also go through **[scripts/test/E2E.md](scripts/test/E2E.md)**.
2. **If a test exists**, run it:
   ```
   pnpm run test:<feature-name>
   ```
   Full suite fallback: `pnpm run test:all`
3. **If no test exists**, create one under `scripts/test/test-<feature-name>.js` before finishing the change.
4. **Always present a results table** to the user after running (auto-printed by `e2e-report.js` for `runSkillTests`; must include **Input**, **Output**, **Status** columns):

| Test | Input | Output | Status |
|------|-------|--------|--------|
| `test-agent-team-e2e` | `new session` | `New session started.` | ✅ Pass |

Never mark a feature done without showing this table.
